WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Good morning, Jacob. Happy Saturday. Here's your week in review

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
for the week of March twenty-second through March twenty-eighth, twenty

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
twenty-six. This was Anthropic's week. If you had to write

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
the screenplay of the best possible seven days a company

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
could have while simultaneously being sued by the Pentagon, you'd

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
write this week and then cut half of it for

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
being unrealistic. A federal judge called the supply-chain designation quote,

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
classic illegal First Amendment retaliation, end quote, and dropped a

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
forty-three-page injunction. Bloomberg reported the company is eyeing an October

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
I-P-O. A misconfigured C-M-S accidentally revealed Claude Mythos, a new

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
model tier above Opus described as, quote, a step change

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
in capabilities, end quote. Apple leaked that iOS twenty-seven will

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
let Claude integrate directly with Siri. And the company's annualized

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
revenue crossed nineteen billion dollars. That's not a week. That's

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
a highlight reel. But this was also the week the

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
Iran war got worse. The Houthis entered the conflict on

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
Saturday, firing ballistic missiles at Israel in their first attack

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
since the Hamas ceasefire. Ten U-S service members were injured

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:16.000
in an Iranian strike on Prince Sultan Air Base in

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
Saudi Arabia. Brent crude hit one hundred twelve dollars and

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
fifty-seven cents, the highest since July twenty twenty-two. And Congress,

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
in a display of timing that belongs in a comedy

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
sketch, rejected the Senate's bipartisan D-H-S funding deal and then

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
left on a two-week recess. Sixty-one thousand unpaid T-S-A workers

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
will be thrilled to hear their representatives are on vacation.

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
Let's start with the highlights. CHAPTER TWO. HIGHLIGHTS AND WINS.

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
You delivered the B-Rs to the Governor's Office on Thursday,

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
which had been escalating across four consecutive briefings. You renewed

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
the GitHub token after six briefings of increasingly desperate reminders.

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
Both of those items are now off the board, and

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
the briefing pipeline is intact. At work, you're back in

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
the rhythm after Spring Break. The legislature returned, the child

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
care subsidy fight is live, and you stayed up past

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
eleven-thirty P-M on Wednesday correcting a sixty-five-page document. Katelyn thought

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
it was, quote, fun to know all this stuff, end

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:24.000
quote. You were less convinced. But the B-Rs got delivered,

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
which means the sixty-five pages paid off. Katelyn is settled

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
back in Tacoma after the eight-day Missouri visit. She switched

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
running shoes from Brooks to Hylo Athletics after a Fleet

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
Feet fitting. She's thirty-six days out from the Tacoma City

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
Half Marathon and in full training mode. She also wants

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
to feed the crows near her place but is worried

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
about the mess, which is the most Katelyn question of

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
the week. CHAPTER THREE. STORIES THAT EVOLVED. Three stories defined

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
this week, and watching them develop across seven daily briefings

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
reveals patterns no single day captured. Story one. Anthropic versus

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
the Pentagon. On Sunday, the hearing was thirty-six hours away

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
and the briefing was tracking the coalition: one hundred fifty

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
retired judges, Microsoft, retired military chiefs. By Tuesday, Judge Rita

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.000
Lin was sharply questioning the Pentagon, asking why the designation

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:24.000
didn't seem, quote, tailored to the stated national security concern,

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
end quote. She found it, quote, pretty surprising, end quote,

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
that the D-O-D argued Hegseth's own directive had no legal

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:36.000
effect. Wednesday brought the Axios Behind the Curtain piece, which

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
was the most important single source on the story since

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:44.000
the lawsuit was filed. It revealed that government officials privately

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.000
want Claude for warfighting, that Anthropic is a big reason

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:52.000
the U-S is six to twelve months ahead of China

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
in A-I for defense, and that the Palantir Maven system

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
officially replacing Anthropic also runs on Claude. Then Thursday, Lin

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:04.000
ruled. Forty-three pages. Classic illegal First Amendment retaliation. Orwellian. Federal

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:08.000
agencies can resume using Claude immediately. The government has until

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:12.000
April second to appeal, which happens to be the same

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.000
day as your Anthropic pilot discussion at work. You can't

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.000
script that kind of timing. Story two. The Iran war

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:24.000
arc. The week opened on Day twenty-three with a forty-eight-hour

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:28.000
ultimatum set to expire Monday evening. Trump deferred the deadline

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:32.000
five days on Monday morning, citing peace talks. Iran said

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.000
he blinked. Krugman sent five newsletters in four days arguing

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:40.000
the U-S entered this war without the willingness to bear

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:44.000
its costs. By midweek, Gulf nations joined the coalition, Iran

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:48.000
cracked open Hormuz for quote, non-hostile, end quote, ships, and

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:52.000
the U-S sent a fifteen-point ceasefire plan demanding full nuclear

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:56.000
dismantlement. Iran rejected it. By Thursday, the Pentagon was developing

00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:00.000
four major escalation scenarios including invading Kharg Island. And Saturday,

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
the Houthis fired on Israel, opening a new front and

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.000
threatening Red Sea shipping lanes. Oil went from about one

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:12.000
hundred two dollars on Tuesday to one hundred twelve on

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:16.000
Saturday. Goldman Sachs says high prices could last through twenty

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:20.000
twenty-seven. The I-E-A called it worse than the nineteen seventies

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:24.000
oil shocks and the Ukraine invasion combined. Story three. The

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:28.000
D-H-S shutdown. Day forty to forty-three. T-S-A workers missed their

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:32.000
third paycheck. Wait times exceeded four hours. Four hundred sixty

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:36.000
officers quit. The Senate passed bipartisan funding at two-twenty A-M

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:40.000
Friday by voice vote, but the House rejected it and

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:44.000
passed their own bill that Senate Democrats called dead on

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:48.000
arrival. Then both chambers left for recess. No resolution is

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:52.000
possible before mid-April. Trump signed an executive order directing immediate

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:56.000
T-S-A pay, but the legal authority is contested and the

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:00.000
officers who quit aren't coming back for an executive order.

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:04.000
CHAPTER FOUR. VAULT ACTIVITY. The vault saw meaningful activity this

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:08.000
week, even if daily note creation was spotty. Three daily

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:12.000
notes were created: March twenty-second, twenty-fifth, and twenty-seventh. The gap

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:16.000
on twenty-third and twenty-fourth tracks with the first days back

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:20.000
at work after Spring Break. The most significant new vault

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:24.000
file was the Anthropic Mythos Capybara Leak note, created March

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:28.000
twenty-seventh. This is a research tracking note for the biggest

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:32.000
Anthropic product news of the month. It includes market impact

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:36.000
data showing cybersecurity stocks dropped five to eleven percent, and

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:40.000
it tracks the Bloomberg I-P-O reporting: October twenty twenty-six at

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:44.000
sixty billion plus. The Riverfront Connector Bridge update was also

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:48.000
created March twenty-seventh, tracking the B-U-I-L-D grant application, the H-B

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:52.000
twenty-one oh-eight land conveyance bill, and the High Street Viaduct

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:56.000
emergency closure. The April seventh election includes a sales tax

00:06:56.000 --> 00:07:00.000
vote tied to this project. The Sunday check-in on March

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:04.000
twenty-second was the first in three weeks, covering the full

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:08.000
Katelyn visit arc and resetting the weekly rhythm. Reading diversity

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:12.000
was flagged at seventy-seven percent A-I and tech content, with

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:16.000
a goal to branch out. CHAPTER FIVE. RELATIONSHIP CHECK. Katelyn

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:20.000
flew home on Sunday the twenty-second after the eight-day Missouri

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:24.000
visit. The long-distance dynamic returned, but the texting stayed warm

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:28.000
and consistent all week. Monday's messages included nine photos and,

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:32.000
quote, miss you and our trip, end quote. Midweek conversations

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:36.000
covered E-Vs, insurance costs, speed bumps near her house, and

00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:40.000
the sixty-five-page document saga. By Friday, she was sharing her

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:44.000
new Hylo Athletics running shoes, bird sightings, and a music

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:48.000
recommendation. She flagged that July time off needs coordination, which

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:52.000
is an open action item. Ben settled up the Friday

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:56.000
family dinner split and confirmed he's arriving Monday for carpet.

00:07:56.000 --> 00:08:00.000
Maggie is getting interested in Claude after Jacob's demo, which

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:04.000
is either flattering or concerning depending on how the demo

00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:08.000
went. The friend group was active. Dustin shared somber news

00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:12.000
on Friday, quote, we lost a good one today, end

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:16.000
quote, with Alex responding, quote, Crossley? Damn, end quote. Context

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:20.000
is incomplete but the tone was heartfelt. On a lighter

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:24.000
note, Dustin got a no-parking sign installed across from his

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:28.000
driveway, which is the most significant infrastructure victory in Jefferson

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:32.000
City since the Capitol got air conditioning. Alex sent Apple

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:36.000
product rankings at eleven P-M on a Friday because Alex's

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:40.000
circadian rhythm runs on Cupertino time. CHAPTER SIX. THE WEEK

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:44.000
AHEAD. This is a loaded week. Here's what's coming. Monday,

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:48.000
March thirtieth. Ben arrives in Jeff City to help with

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:52.000
carpet. No work events scheduled, but the legislature is in

00:08:52.000 --> 00:08:56.000
session. Tuesday, March thirty-first. Payday. Carpet install, nine A-M to

00:08:56.000 --> 00:09:00.000
two P-M. This is the final home project in this

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:04.000
cycle. After this, the condo is in a settled state

00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:08.000
for the first time since January. Wednesday, April first. Q-two

00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:12.000
starts. Karen announces retirement at eleven A-M. Hiring projects begin

00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:16.000
immediately after. Apple turns fifty. It's going to be a

00:09:16.000 --> 00:09:20.000
big news day across every beat. Thursday, April second. The

00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:24.000
big day. Anthropic pilot discussion at nine A-M. This is

00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:28.000
your chance to make the case for Claude at work

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:32.000
while the legal cloud is lifting. Prep with the Claude

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:36.000
pilot explainer note from Apple Notes, the Learning Curves report,

00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:40.000
and Judge Lin's ruling highlights. Also Thursday: dinner with Alex,

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:44.000
Chris, and Dustin at six P-M, Katelyn's off day, and

00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:48.000
the government's appeal deadline on the Anthropic ruling. That's a

00:09:48.000 --> 00:09:52.000
lot of load-bearing calendar space for one Thursday. Friday, April

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:56.000
third. Regular work day. Legislative session continues. May fifteenth last

00:09:56.000 --> 00:10:00.000
day of session is forty-four days out. Other dates to

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:04.000
watch: May third, Katelyn and Jenn run the Tacoma City

00:10:04.000 --> 00:10:08.000
Half Marathon. May ninth, your Capital City Race. June eighth,

00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:12.000
W-W-D-C. July twenty-third, you in Washington. CHAPTER SEVEN. WHAT TO

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:16.000
WATCH. Three things to keep your eye on this week.

00:10:16.000 --> 00:10:20.000
First, the government's Anthropic appeal decision. The deadline is Thursday.

00:10:20.000 --> 00:10:24.000
If they appeal, the Ninth Circuit hears it within weeks.

00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:28.000
If they don't, the injunction holds while the full case

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:32.000
proceeds. Either way, this will shape the mood of your

00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:36.000
pilot discussion Thursday morning. Second, the Houthi Red Sea impact.

00:10:36.000 --> 00:10:40.000
If Houthi forces resume targeting commercial shipping, the Iran war

00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:44.000
premium on oil gets a second logistics premium on top.

00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:48.000
Goldman's fourteen to eighteen dollar per barrel risk estimate may

00:10:48.000 --> 00:10:52.000
prove conservative. Watch Monday's oil open. Third, Apple's fiftieth anniversary.

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:56.000
Wednesday is going to be wall-to-wall Apple coverage. The Siri

00:10:56.000 --> 00:11:00.000
Extensions story, the Mac Pro death, the I-P-O pipeline for

00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:04.000
the industry, and whatever celebration Apple has planned at Apple

00:11:04.000 --> 00:11:08.000
Park. John Ternus, the heir-apparent C-E-O, will reportedly be center

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:12.000
stage. CHAPTER EIGHT. CLOSING. Here's the thing about this week,

00:11:12.000 --> 00:11:16.000
Jacob. On paper, it was one of the most consequential

00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:20.000
weeks of twenty twenty-six. A federal judge issued a landmark

00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:24.000
A-I governance ruling. The Houthis opened a new front in

00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:28.000
a war that's already reshaping global energy. Congress left sixty-one

00:11:28.000 --> 00:11:32.000
thousand workers unpaid and went on vacation. Oil hit highs

00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:36.000
not seen since twenty twenty-two. But in your life, the

00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:40.000
week was quieter than the headlines suggest. You went back

00:11:40.000 --> 00:11:44.000
to work after Spring Break. You corrected sixty-five pages. You

00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:48.000
renewed a GitHub token. You watched from a distance as

00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:52.000
a judge in San Francisco said the things you'd been

00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:56.000
hoping she'd say. Katelyn switched running shoes. Ben figured out

00:11:56.000 --> 00:12:00.000
the dinner split. Dustin got a parking sign. The next

00:12:00.000 --> 00:12:04.000
week is where all the threads converge. Carpet on Tuesday.

00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:08.000
Retirement on Wednesday. Anthropic on Thursday. Friends on Thursday night.

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:12.000
The condo gets settled. Q-two begins. And somewhere between the

00:12:12.000 --> 00:12:16.000
pilot discussion and the dinner reservation, you'll find out whether

00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:20.000
the government wants to fight a forty-three-page ruling or let

00:12:20.000 --> 00:12:24.000
it stand. The carpet installers arrive at nine. The hiring

00:12:24.000 --> 00:12:28.000
projects start at eleven. The appeal deadline is at close

00:12:28.000 --> 00:12:32.000
of business. It's a week where the personal infrastructure and

00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:36.000
the professional infrastructure are being built at the same time,

00:12:36.000 --> 00:12:40.000
which, if you think about it, is the whole Year

00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:44.000
of Integration in miniature. Enjoy the Saturday, Jacob. It's sixty

00:12:44.000 --> 00:12:48.000
degrees and sunny. Go outside. The carpet can't install itself

00:12:48.000 --> 00:12:52.000
until Tuesday, and neither can you. This has been your

00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:56.000
weekly briefing for the week of March twenty-second through twenty-eighth.

00:12:56.000 --> 00:12:58.000
Talk to you Monday morning.
